88/*
89 * DHCP context structure
90 * This holds the libisc information for a dhcp entity
91 */
92
93typedef struct dhcp_context {
94 isc_mem_t *mctx;
95 isc_appctx_t *actx;
96 int actx_started;
97 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr;
98 isc_task_t *task;
99 isc_socketmgr_t *socketmgr;
100 isc_timermgr_t *timermgr;
101#if defined (NSUPDATE)
102 dns_client_t *dnsclient;
103 int use_local4;
104 isc_sockaddr_t local4_sockaddr;
105 int use_local6;
106 isc_sockaddr_t local6_sockaddr;
107#endif
108} dhcp_context_t;
109
110extern dhcp_context_t dhcp_gbl_ctx;
111
112#define DHCP_MAXDNS_WIRE 256
113#define DHCP_MAXNS 3
114#define DHCP_HMAC_MD5_NAME "HMAC-MD5.SIG-ALG.REG.INT."
115#define DHCP_HMAC_SHA1_NAME "HMAC-SHA1.SIG-ALG.REG.INT."
116#define DHCP_HMAC_SHA224_NAME "HMAC-SHA224.SIG-ALG.REG.INT."
117#define DHCP_HMAC_SHA256_NAME "HMAC-SHA256.SIG-ALG.REG.INT."
118#define DHCP_HMAC_SHA384_NAME "HMAC-SHA384.SIG-ALG.REG.INT."
119#define DHCP_HMAC_SHA512_NAME "HMAC-SHA512.SIG-ALG.REG.INT."
120
121isc_result_t dhcp_isc_name(unsigned char *namestr,
